  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (env-gap variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The pump is deployed in operating-theatre environments subject to temperature drift (18–26 °C), variable ambient pressure (altitude-capable theatres, 85–101 kPa), and electromagnetic interference from electrosurgical units. All validation activities were conducted in a controlled laboratory at 22 °C and standard atmospheric pressure; no environmental-sensitivity study has been performed and the operating envelope does not bound these environmental parameters.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-req",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-claim",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/morrison-cfd-hemolysis-v2",
